5049fig20.jpeg" height="1229" width="1800" aria-labelledby="fig20" loading="lazy" /><figcaption><span class="heading">Figure 20</span> Analysis of myocardial TPC. Superimposition of the TMF curve and the tissue velocity curve highlights the usefulness of TPC. In cases of impaired relaxation, E and Ea both decrease. Thus, the E/Ea ratio is normal, as is LV filling pressure. In cases of a pseudonormal TMF pattern, E remains normal whereas Ea decreases. Thus, the E/Ea ratio and LV filling pressures are both increased. In cases of a restrictive TMF pattern, E increases whereas Ea decreases. Thus, the E/Ea ratio and LV filling pressures are both increased.<div class="core-figure-tools"><ul><li><a class="core-figure-download-powerpoint" href="/action/downloadFigures?doi=10.1148%2Frg.311105049&amp;id=fig20">Download as PowerPoint</a></li></ul></div></figcaption></figure></div></section><section id="bibliography" role="doc-bibliography"><h2>References</h2><div role="list"><div role="listitem"><div id="r1" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">1Karamitsos TD, Francis JM, Myerson S, Selvanayagam JB, Neubauer S. The role of cardiovascular magnetic resonance imaging in heart failure. <em>J Am Coll Cardiol</em> 2009;54(15):1407–1424.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jacc.2009.04.094">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19796734/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=The+role+of+cardiovascular+magnetic+resonance+imaging+in+heart+failure&amp;author=TD+Karamitsos&amp;author=JM+Francis&amp;author=S+Myerson&amp;author=JB+Selvanayagam&amp;author=S+Neubauer&amp;publication_year=2009&amp;journal=J+Am+Coll+Cardiol&amp;pages=1407-1424&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.jacc.2009.04.094&amp;pmid=19796734">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem"><div c